{"id": 231963272, "title": "PSNI \u201cgrowing increasingly concerned\u201d for man not seen since Thursday afternoon", "text": "Police are \u201cgrowing increasingly concerned\u201d for a man not seen since Thursday afternoon. In a statement issued on Sunday afternoon, the PSNI said they are concerned for the welfare of missing person, 55-year-old Stephen Watterson. A police spokesman said: \u201cStephen was last seen walking into Magherafelt town centre at approximately 2pm on Thursday, 6th June in the Rainey Street area. Read more: Viral video of man on ladder with 'gun' leads to arrest Read more: Drugs worth estimated \u00a3600k seized in \u201csophisticated cannabis factory\u201d raid \u201cHe is described as being approximately 5\u2019 6\u201d, of stocky build with short or shaven black hair, and he has brown eyes. It\u2019s understood Stephen was last seen wearing jeans, dark trainers and a dark top or a bomber-type style jacket. \u201cIf you have any information in relation to his whereabouts or you believe you may have seen him, please contact police on 101, quoting reference number 1603 08/06/24.\u201d For all the latest news, visit the Belfast Live homepage here and sign up to our daily newsletter here.", "summary": "Stephen Watterson last seen walking into Magherafelt town centre", "url": "https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/psni-growing-increasingly-concerned-man-29321503", "image": "https://i2-prod.belfastlive.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/article29321494.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Stephen-Watterson.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 12:22:45", "author": "Maurice Fitzmaurice", "authors": ["Maurice Fitzmaurice"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.489}